Key Match Events: Karl-Anthony Towns had 27 points and 13 rebounds.
Josh Hart added 21 points and 11 rebounds.
Immanuel Quickley scored 22 points against his former team.
Scottie Barnes had 18 points for the Raptors.
RJ Barrett, another former Knick, had 16 points.
Mikal Bridges had 10 points as all five Knicks starters scored in double digits.

New York led 91-81 with 9:22 left in the fourth quarter after a basket from Barnes and followed with a 15-0 run during a five-minute stretch in which the Raptors missed eight shots and had two turnovers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Knicks have won their last seven meetings against Toronto dating back to last season. New York’s last loss to the Raptors was Jan. 22, 2023, at Madison Square Garden.
